request.description:
🔐 SCAN ENCRYPTED QR - CLIENT-SIDE DECRYPTION

This endpoint returns the encrypted payload WITHOUT decrypting it.
Your app decrypts it locally using the master key from login.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

EXAMPLE RESPONSE:
{
  "qr_type": "encrypted",
  "raw_encrypted_payload": "ZT-qd7Fc6BRd-CvBT7diT37Ri0rtSc26r2oNG8I3w_Q...",
  "portal_url": "http://localhost:3000/verify?token=e3112bb8..."
}

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

CLIENT-SIDE DECRYPTION CODE:

// STEP 1: You already have from login:
const masterEncryptionKey = "decrypted-from-encrypted_enc_key";
const portal_url = "http://localhost:3000/verify?token=...";

// STEP 2: Derive per-QR AES key
const perQrKeyMaterial = masterEncryptionKey + portal_url;
const perQrKeyHash = await crypto.subtle.digest(
  "SHA-256",
  new TextEncoder().encode(perQrKeyMaterial)
);

const perQrAesKey = await crypto.subtle.importKey(
  "raw",
  perQrKeyHash,
  { name: "AES-GCM" },
  false,
  ["decrypt"]
);

// STEP 3: Decrypt raw_encrypted_payload
function base64urlToArrayBuffer(base64url) {
  const base64 = base64url.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/');
  const binary = atob(base64);
  const bytes = new Uint8Array(binary.length);
  for (let i = 0; i < binary.length; i++) {
    bytes[i] = binary.charCodeAt(i);
  }
  return bytes.buffer;
}

const encPayloadBuffer = base64urlToArrayBuffer(raw_encrypted_payload);
const payloadNonce = encPayloadBuffer.slice(0, 12);
const payloadCiphertext = encPayloadBuffer.slice(12);

const decryptedPayload = await crypto.subtle.decrypt(
  { name: "AES-GCM", iv: payloadNonce },
  perQrAesKey,
  payloadCiphertext
);

const verifyUrl = new TextDecoder().decode(decryptedPayload);
console.log("Decrypted URL:", verifyUrl);

// STEP 4: Open in WebView
webView.loadUrl(verifyUrl);

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

🔒 SECURITY:
- Server NEVER sees your decryption key
- Each QR has unique per-QR key
- Can't decrypt without user password
- HDFC-level security

Test this endpoint first, then use the code above to decrypt!

🔐 OPTIONAL - PKI-verified Decryption (Highest Security)

Decrypt QR with device signature verification (like HDFC).

**When to use:**
- When device certificate is registered
- Adds hardware-backed security
- Server verifies device signature

**Headers:**
- Authorization: JWT token
- X-Device-Signature: RSA-PSS signature of request body
- X-Device-ID: Device UUID from registration

**Signature Calculation:**
```javascript
// Sign the JSON body with device private key
const message = JSON.stringify(body);
const signature = crypto.subtle.sign(
  { name: "RSA-PSS", saltLength: 32 },
  devicePrivateKey,
  new TextEncoder().encode(message)
);
const signatureHex = Array.from(new Uint8Array(signature))
  .map(b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, '0')).join('');
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "document": { ... },
  "portal_url": "http://localhost:3000/verify?token=..."
}
```

**Note:** This is OPTIONAL. Use "Scan QR - Client Decrypt" endpoint for simpler flow without device registration.
